{{WorldSeriesRt}}
The '''[[1953 in baseball|1953]] [[World Series]]''' matched the four-time defending champion [[New York Yankees]] against the [[Los Angeles Dodgers|Brooklyn Dodgers]] in a rematch of the [[1952 World Series|1952 Series]]. The Yankees won in six games for their fifth straight title &ndash; a mark which has not been equalled &ndash; and their 16<sup>th</sup> overall. [[Billy Martin]] recorded his 12<sup>th</sup> hit of the series scoring [[Hank Bauer]] in Game 6, and won the Series MVP.

Although the Yankees won the Series, Brooklyn pitcher [[Carl Erskine]] set a Series record by striking out 14 Yankees in Game 3 (a record which has since been broken).

'''Records:''' [[New York Yankees]] (W: 99, L: 52, Pct: .656, GA: 8 <U+00BD>) - [[Brooklyn Dodgers]] (W: 105, L: 49, Pct: .682, GA: 13)

'''Managers:''' [[Casey Stengel]] (New York), [[Chuck Dressen]] (Brooklyn)

'''Umpires:''' [[Bill Grieve]] (AL), [[Bill Stewart (sports)|Bill Stewart]] (NL), [[Eddie Hurley]] (AL), [[Artie Gore]] (NL), [[Hank Soar]] (AL: outfield only), [[Frank Dascoli]] (NL: outfield only)

'''Television:''' [[NBC]] ([[Mel Allen]] and [[Vin Scully]] announcing)

