==Trivia==
* The [[Brooklyn Dodgers]] batted exactly .300 as a team, yet lost. This was the ninth time in [[World Series]] history where a losing team had a better team [[batting average]] and only the fifth time a team batted at least .300.

* On October 2, 1953, [[Yogi Berra]] was struck twice by pitcher [[Carl Erskine]] making him the first [[American League]] player in [[World Series]] history to be a hit-batsman twice during the same game.

* During Game 3, [[Carl Erskine]] mowed down fourteen (14) batters for a new [[World Series]] single game record <U+2014> one later beaten by [[Bob Gibson]] with seventeen (17) in game one of the [[1968 World Series]].

* Dropping their seventh [[World Series]] without a victory, the Dodgers terminated manager [[Chuck Dressen]]'s contract who was demanding two more years.  [[Walter Alston]] would take his place and manage the Dodgers for the next 23 seasons (1954-1976) before being replaced by [[Tommy Lasorda]].

